Bill Kendrick (http://www.newbreedsoftware.com/bill/) lived in Davis from 1998 to 2004. In that time, he helped co-found and run the ["LUGOD" Linux Users' Group of Davis], worked from home for a bit, and worked for MCI/WorldCom in Sacramento for a bit.

''As of December 2004'', he lives in Mountain View with his wife Melissa (a graduate of ["UC Davis" UC Davis'] Linguistics dept.) and works in Palo Alto writing games for cellphones.

He also writes Open Source software for Linux, Windows, Mac and other platforms as a hobby.
See: http://www.newbreedsoftware.com/

